  m_text: "\t- Paired tags in HTML are tags that come in an opening and a closing
    form and wrap around content. For example, <p> and </p> are used to create a
    paragraph of text, while <h1> and </h1> are used to define a main heading. These
    tags work as a pair to tell the browser where the content starts and ends."
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 5302535af1044152a457ed104f1f4b91, type: 2}
